❯ In this Unity project, I want the main feature to be cutting mesh objects     
  with arbitrary planes. In this session, please implement a feature that       
  slices any given Mesh with a plane.                                           
  Given a Mesh and a plane represented by Unity.Mathematics.Geometry.Plane, the 
   system should cut the mesh along the plane, generate two separate meshes,    
  and cap the cut surfaces on both sides.                                       
  Please first implement the feature in C#, along with appropriate tests. Use   
  Unity’s standard Test Runner to perform functional testing. In addition,      
  render the generated meshes in a scene using Mesh Renderers and perform       
  qualitative visual validation using your own (AI agent) visual inspection.    
  Please also prepare high-load test cases and measure performance.             
  After completing the C# implementation and evaluation, create a               
  Burst-optimized version and compare its performance against the original      
  implementation.                                                               

