⏺ Now I'll write the managed slicer. The design uses:
  - One pass to classify vertices by signed distance, snapping d ≥ 0 to the
  positive side
  - Per-edge intersection cache (so each cut edge produces one shared vertex
  pair across triangles that share it)
  - Cut segments collected per side, walked into closed loops, fan-triangulated
  for caps
  - Cap vertices duplicated with plane-normal (hard edge at cut)

