⏺ Found the bug: the cap loop walker uses per-side vertex indices, but Unity
  primitive cubes duplicate vertices per face, so cap intersections at corners
  (where two side faces meet) become two separate vertices that aren't
  connected. The graph fragments into per-face mini-loops. Let me fix this with
  position-based dedup.

