  The Burst version is consistently faster, but only by ~1.2–1.45× because Mesh
  I/O (managed Vector3[] marshalling for Mesh.vertices/normals/tangents) and the
   C# Dictionary-based cap walker run in both implementations. The
  Burst-resident slice loop scales linearly with triangle count. Larger speedups
   would require switching to MeshDataArray/SetVertexBufferData zero-copy I/O
  and pushing the cap walker into Burst with NativeHashMap adjacency — natural
  next step if needed.

